   Vertical Wave

   Evocative collage


   To the seagull
   above
   the pinewoods
   of the coast,
   on the wind
   the sibilant
   syllable of my ode.
   Pablo Neruda

                      Walking to the ocean


                                                 A la gaviota
                                                 sobre
                                                 los piñares
                                                 de la costa,
                                                 en el viento
                                                 la sílaba
                                                 silbante de mi oda.
                                                 Pablo Neruda


   Here, in this little Bay,
   Full of tumultuous life and great repose,
   Where, twice a day,
   The purposeless, glad ocean comes and goes
   Under high cliffs, and far from the huge town,
   I sit me down.

   Coventry Patmore
